## All variants processed
#generate popmap file. Two column popmap with the same format as stacks, and the columns must be named 'id' and 'pop'
popmap<-data.frame(id=colnames(all_species@gt)[2:length(colnames(all_species@gt))],pop=substr(colnames(all_species@gt)[2:length(colnames(all_species@gt))], 1,4))

# make cinereus complex popmap
popmap.cinereus.complex <- popmap[!popmap$pop %in% c("SOMO", "SONV", "SOPA", "SOVA", "SOTR"),]

# Get rid of SOCI and SOJE that are actually (probably) SOMO:
# SOCI_DMNS_14627, SOCI_UAM_79491, SOJE_MSB_150524
popmap.cinereus.complex <- popmap.cinereus.complex[!popmap.cinereus.complex$id %in% c("SOCI_DMNS_14627", "SOCI_UAM_79491", "SOJE_MSB_150524"),]

# Get rid of SOJE that is actually (probably) SONA:
# SOJE_MSB_264232
#popmap.cinereus.complex <- popmap.cinereus.complex[!popmap.cinereus.complex$id %in% c("SOJE_MSB_264232"),]

# subset vcf for only cinereus complex
vcfR.cinereus.complex <- min_mac(all_species[samples = popmap.cinereus.complex$id], min.mac = 1)
## 28.01% of SNPs fell below a minor allele count of 1 and were removed from the VCF

#visualize distributions
hard_filter(vcfR=vcfR.cinereus.complex)
## no depth cutoff provided, exploratory visualization will be generated.

## no genotype quality cutoff provided, exploratory visualization will be generated.

## ***** Object of Class vcfR *****
## 394 samples
## 234 CHROMs
## 106,701 variants
## Object size: 498.1 Mb
## 69.5 percent missing data
## *****        *****         *****
# hard filter to minimum depth of 5, minimum genotype quality of 30
vcfR.cinereus.complex_filter <- hard_filter(vcfR=vcfR.cinereus.complex, depth = 5, gq = 30)
## 40.15% of genotypes fall below a read depth of 5 and were converted to NA
## 1.79% of genotypes fall below a genotype quality of 30 and were converted to NA
# allele balance filter
vcfR.cinereus.complex_filter <- filter_allele_balance(vcfR.cinereus.complex_filter)
## 6.82% of het genotypes (0.17% of all genotypes) fall outside of 0.25 - 0.75 allele balance ratio and were converted to NA

#visualize and pick appropriate max depth cutoff
max_depth(vcfR.cinereus.complex_filter)
## cutoff is not specified, exploratory visualization will be generated.

## dashed line indicates a mean depth across all SNPs of 11.8

vcfR.cinereus.complex_filter <- max_depth(vcfR.cinereus.complex_filter, maxdepth = 50)
## maxdepth cutoff is specified, filtered vcfR object will be returned
## 0.06% of SNPs were above a mean depth of 50 and were removed from the vcf

#run function to visualize samples above the threshold we want from the vcf
missing_by_sample(vcfR=vcfR.cinereus.complex_filter, popmap = popmap.cinereus.complex)

#add outgroup individual back in
filtered.snps <- rownames(extract.gt(vcfR.cinereus.complex_filter_thin))
original.snps <- rownames(extract.gt(all_species))
logical.slicer <- original.snps %in% filtered.snps
index.slicer <- (1:length(original.snps))[logical.slicer]
vcfR.with.outgroup_filter_thin <- all_species[index.slicer]
#check correct snps chosen
identical(rownames(extract.gt(vcfR.with.outgroup_filter_thin)), rownames(extract.gt(vcfR.cinereus.complex_filter_thin)))

#see which outgroup individual would have least missing data
identical(colnames(extract.gt(vcfR.with.outgroup_filter_thin[samples = popmap_filter$id])), colnames(extract.gt(vcfR.cinereus.complex_filter_thin)))
## [1] TRUE
vcfR.all <- vcfR.with.outgroup_filter_thin[samples = popmap$id]

# hard filter to minimum depth of 5, minimum genotype quality of 30

## 0.6% of genotypes fall below a genotype quality of 30 and were converted to NA
